import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts()
    group_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Group')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of groups in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    group_counts = data.groupby('group')['person'].count()
    group_counts.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    plt.xlabel('Group')
    plt.ylabel('Number of People')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people in each group?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    group_person_counts = data.groupby(['group', 'person']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)
    sns.heatmap(group_person_counts, annot=True, fmt="d", cmap="YlGnBu")
    plt.title("What is the most common group-person combination in the dataset?")
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
